%N A398024 Number of fixed 3-convex polyominoes with perimeter 2*n.
%C A398024 The conjectured result has since been proved by Thomas Prellberg, though the proof is still being examined as it's quite complex. [Anthony J. Guttmann]
%H A398024 Andrew R. Conway and Anthony J. Guttmann, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2606.13845">k-Convex Polyominoes by Semi-perimeter</a>, arXiv:2606.13845 [cs.DM], Jul 17 2026.
%F A398024 G.f.: x^2*(8*x^6 - 34*x^5 + 97*x^4 - 110*x^3 + 54*x^2 - 12*x + 1) / ((1-4*x)^2 * (1-2*x) * (2*x^2 - 4*x + 1)) - (1-3*x)^2 * x^4 / ((1-4*x)^(3/2) * (1-2*x) * (2*x^2 - 4*x + 1)). (Conjectured by Conway and Guttmann (2026).)
%F A398024 For asymptotics see Conway and Guttmann (2026).
